            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>92</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>121</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... walking a road, a rough, dry ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>89</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>118</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>152</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967c"/><citedRange>177</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>261</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>32</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>242</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970"/><citedRange>275</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>102</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>91, 99, 102</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>84, 164, 405, 406, 408</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In the Tsappra-tune: conscious beings keep the rules of self-discipline and do not transgress them because of passion ... the property of others ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Verständige Menschen bewahren die Regel der Selbstzucht.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Conscious beings keep the rule of self-discipline.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>84</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die verständigen Wesen nehmen anderen nicht [ihr] Eigentum [fort].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Prudent beings do not take [away] the property of others.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>406</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die verständigen Wesen nehmen anderen nicht das Leben [und] verletzen nicht die Grenze des Samvara.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Prudent beings do not take the life of others [and] do not violate the constraints of the samvara.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>408</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Verständige Wesen wahren die Regel des Saṃvara [und] überschreiten [sie] nicht aus Leidenschaft.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Prudent beings keep the rule of the saṃvara [and] do not transgress [it] out of passion.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>405</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die bedachtsamen Wesen nehmen anderen nicht das Leben [und] verletzen nicht die Grenze des Saṃvara.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The thoughtful beings do not take the life of others [and] do not violate the boundaries of the saṃvara.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>164</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wer mit ... Ehrerbietung die Füße des Buddha verehrt, den Samen des Nirvāṇas in [seine] Geburtenfolge gesät habend, der wird(?) [in dem Gedanken]: "Du bist mein Verwandter" [als] Verwandter begehrt. Wer...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever] reveres with ... reverence the feet of the Buddha, having sown the seed of the nirvāṇa in the sequence of [his] incarnations, he will be desired as a relative [with the thought]: "You are my relative." Who ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>244</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
